<br />
<br />I did this awhile ago using a very simple CPLD and the NES CPU and some other thingies.  It's called "HardNES" and pics of it can be found here:  
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://tripoint.org/kevtris/Projects/hardnes/index.html">http://tripoint.org/kevtris/Projects/hardnes/index.html</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />I was thinking some day it'd be nice to make another one with more sound chips and such, but it never happened.  These days, I guess I could make it on an FPGA using that NES FPGA core I have designed.

		

