	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The 2A03 contains the NES CPU and APU. The only way you can write to the APU is through the CPU, so you'll need to provide some memory for the program and have that read some external source for data and write to the APU.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


